01:09:10,840 --> 01:09:12,558
Yeah. Right.

1228
01:09:12,920 --> 01:09:14,956
It's me that's the fantasist.

1229
01:09:15,080 --> 01:09:18,755
I wanted to believe that you had a son,
so I let my imagination run riot.

1230
01:09:18,840 --> 01:09:20,910
Obviously I played a part, I can see that.

1231
01:09:21,000 --> 01:09:24,629
No! Not at all.
I met you and I thought, "Cute guy.

1232
01:09:24,720 --> 01:09:27,871
"God, if only he had a son.
A geeky, teenage kid, if possible."

1233
01:09:27,960 --> 01:09:30,679
Then you turned up at my house
with Marcus, and bingo!

1234
01:09:30,760 --> 01:09:35,151
Now I made this crazy link
'cause of some deep psychological need in me.

1235
01:09:36,000 --> 01:09:38,594
You shouldn't beat yourself up about it.

1236
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,870
It could have happened to anyone.

1237
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:49,995
The first time I met you
I thought you were a bit blank.

1238
01:09:52,400 --> 01:09:54,595
But then you changed my mind.

1239
01:09:56,000 --> 01:09:57,831
Maybe I was right.

1240
01:09:58,320 --> 01:10:00,117
-Rachel, listen.
-Yes?

1241
01:10:01,200 --> 01:10:02,997
[Poignant piano note]

1242
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:12,396
I'm sorry, you're right.

1243
01:10:15,960 --> 01:10:20,078
I am a blank.

1244
01:10:21,640 --> 01:10:25,428
I'm really nothing.

1245
01:10:29,680 --> 01:10:33,195
I don't know what the hell I was thinking of,
I'm sorry.

1246
01:10:33,280 --> 01:10:35,271
[Melancholy piano music]

1247
01:10:53,520 --> 01:10:54,509
'Bye, Ellie.

1248
01:10:54,600 --> 01:10:56,192
Marcus! My man!

1249
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:58,275
SlMON: 'Bye, Marcus!

1250
01:10:58,360 --> 01:10:59,952
CLASSMATE: See you, Marcus!

1251
01:11:00,040 --> 01:11:02,031
[Piano music continues]

1252
01:11:16,440 --> 01:11:18,032
[Fiona cries]

1253
01:11:18,440 --> 01:11:19,509
Mum?

1254
01:11:19,600 --> 01:11:21,591
[Melancholy rock song]

1255
01:11:43,840 --> 01:11:48,550
TEACHER: So, if z = 17, does x > 2?

1256
01:11:48,920 --> 01:11:50,239
Marcus?

1257
01:11:51,680 --> 01:11:53,830
MARCUS: I didn't know what the answer was.

1258
01:11:53,920 --> 01:11:55,990
I didn't know what "x" equaled.

1259
01:11:56,080 --> 01:11:58,310
And I didn't know how to help my mum.

1260
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:09,592
MARCUS: And then I realized.

1261
01:12:09,680 --> 01:12:12,399
There was something she said
I could do for her.

1262
01:12:12,480 --> 01:12:17,031
-I'm thinking of singing at the school concert.
-You? At the rock concert?

1263
01:12:17,720 --> 01:12:21,030
I don't think that would be
a very good idea, Marcus.

1264
01:12:21,120 --> 01:12:22,439
Will you accompany me?

1265
01:12:22,520 --> 01:12:24,397
All I've got is a tambourine.

1266
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:28,197
No, I'm sorry. It's suicide.

1267
01:12:29,680 --> 01:12:32,069
I mean, they'll crucify you.

1268
01:12:33,160 --> 01:12:35,754
[Melancholy piano music]

1269
01:12:38,160 --> 01:12:39,752
[Doorbell rings]

1270
01:12:55,920 --> 01:12:57,592
Mum's at it again.

1271
01:13:00,760 --> 01:13:03,558
-At what? Sorry.
-What do you mean, what?

1272
01:13:04,640 --> 01:13:05,834
The crying.

1273
01:13:05,920 --> 01:13:08,354
She sits in the house all day, crying.

1274
01:13:08,440 --> 01:13:10,829
She does it in the mornings, too.

1275
01:13:13,720 --> 01:13:18,077
It's as bad now as it was
before the Dead Duck Day.

1276
01:13:23,560 --> 01:13:26,313
Marcus, I'm sorry, mate...

1277
01:13:28,560 --> 01:13:30,312
...I'm a bit busy at the moment.

1278
01:13:30,400 --> 01:13:33,312
You're busy? Doing what?

1279
01:13:35,600 --> 01:13:37,989
-Didn't you hear me?
-I heard you.

1280
01:13:38,160 --> 01:13:41,311
-What do you want me to do about it?
-I don't know.

1281
01:13:41,400 --> 01:13:43,868
-You could talk to her.
-Yeah? And what would I say?

1282
01:13:43,960 --> 01:13:46,030
-I don't know!
-Why would she listen to me?

1283
01:13:46,120 --> 01:13:47,712
Who am I to her?

1284
01:13:48,400 --> 01:13:50,118
-I'm nobody.
-You're not nobody.

1285
01:13:50,200 --> 01:13:52,430
-You're--
-Who? Who do you think I am?

1286
01:13:53,520 --> 01:13:54,839
Who do you think you are?

1287
01:13:54,920 --> 01:13:58,708
You come here uninvited,
you disrupt my life, you screw things up.

1288
01:13:59,240 --> 01:14:01,708
What do you want from me?
This isn't my problem.

1289
01:14:01,800 --> 01:14:04,553
I'm not your family, mate. I'm not.
I'm not your uncle.

1290
01:14:04,640 --> 01:14:05,834
I'm not your big brother.

1291
01:14:05,920 --> 01:14:09,230
We've established pretty firmly
that I'm not your father, either, am l?

1292
01:14:09,320 --> 01:14:10,150
But....

1293
01:14:10,240 --> 01:14:11,514
I'll tell you what I am.

1294
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:15,798
I'm the guy who's really good at
choosing trainers or records, okay?

1295
01:14:15,880 --> 01:14:18,440
That's it. I can't help you with real things.

1296
01:14:18,600 --> 01:14:21,876
I can't help you with anything
that means anything.

1297
01:14:24,160 --> 01:14:25,798
You could try.

1298
01:14:34,960 --> 01:14:36,154
You're right.

1299
01:14:36,840 --> 01:14:38,273
You can't help me.

1300
01:14:38,360 --> 01:14:39,713
How could you?

1301
01:14:39,800 --> 01:14:42,394
You're a stupid person who watches TV all day...

1302
01:14:42,480 --> 01:14:43,435
...and buys things.

1303
01:14:43,520 --> 01:14:47,832
You don't give a shit about anybody,
and nobody gives a shit about you!

1304
01:14:52,920 --> 01:14:55,309
[Door opens and slams shut]

1305
01:15:07,000 --> 01:15:09,594
[Acoustic guitar]

1306
01:15:10,680 --> 01:15:13,274
[Upbeat rock music]

1307
01:15:17,280 --> 01:15:20,238
MARCUS: Mum said my singing brought
sunshine and happiness...

1308
01:15:20,320 --> 01:15:21,719
...into her life.

1309
01:15:21,960 --> 01:15:25,077
So I'd do it, even if it meant mine was over.

1310
01:15:53,720 --> 01:15:54,789
Look, Mum.

1311
01:16:08,320 --> 01:16:10,311
[Rock song continues]

1312
01:16:35,760 --> 01:16:40,709
WlLL: My life is made up of units of time.
Buying CDs: Two units.

1313
01:16:42,320 --> 01:16:44,880
Eating lunch: Three units.

1314
01:16:46,960 --> 01:16:50,077
Exercising: Two units.

1315
01:16:52,440 --> 01:16:54,954
All in all, I had a very full life.

1316
01:17:04,440 --> 01:17:08,433
WlLL: It's just that it didn't mean anything.

1317
01:17:15,320 --> 01:17:19,518
[Combination of the continuing rock song
and Santa's Super Sleigh]

1318
01:17:20,920 --> 01:17:26,392
[CD player] "Look who's coming
round the bend"

1319
01:17:34,280 --> 01:17:38,239
WlLL: The fact was there was only one thing
that meant something to me:

1320
01:17:38,920 --> 01:17:40,512
[Doorbell rings]

1321
01:17:49,760 --> 01:17:53,389
WlLL: Marcus. He was the only thing
that meant something to me.

1322
01:17:53,880 --> 01:17:56,758
And Fiona was the only thing
that meant something to him.

1323
01:17:56,840 --> 01:17:59,149
And she was about to fall off the edge.

1324
01:17:59,640 --> 01:18:01,232
[Doorbell rings]

1325
01:18:02,920 --> 01:18:04,911
[Rock music continues]

1326
01:18:17,120 --> 01:18:19,236
ALL: Single parents alone together!

1327
01:18:19,320 --> 01:18:21,231
Single parents alone together!

1328
01:18:21,320 --> 01:18:25,518
Single parents alone together!
All for one and one for all!

1329
01:18:27,720 --> 01:18:30,792
-Fiona!
-Will, we haven't seen you for a while.

1330
01:18:30,920 --> 01:18:32,239
How's Ned?

1331
01:18:32,720 --> 01:18:36,952
Who? He's a load of crap. He doesn't exist.

1332
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:39,433
Yeah, I made him up.

1333
01:18:39,520 --> 01:18:40,919
-You made him up?
-Yeah.

1334
01:18:41,000 --> 01:18:43,434
-To meet women.
-You're sick.

1335
01:18:44,320 --> 01:18:46,550
-Fiona, I've got to talk to you.
-Go ahead.

1336
01:18:46,640 --> 01:18:49,359
No, you know, properly talk to you, privately.

1337
01:18:49,440 --> 01:18:52,398
No, this is a circle of truth.

1338
01:18:52,480 --> 01:18:55,916
Whatever you have to say,
you can say it in front of everybody.

1339
01:18:56,880 --> 01:19:01,032
Okay. Please don't try
and commit suicide again.

1340
01:19:03,640 --> 01:19:06,757
I can't believe you just said that.
That is my private experience.

1341
01:19:06,840 --> 01:19:09,479
Yeah, well, that's the thing, isn't it? It's not.

1342
01:19:09,560 --> 01:19:11,073
Marcus is worried about you.

1343
01:19:11,160 --> 01:19:13,116
I'm worried because he's worried about you.

1344
01:19:13,200 --> 01:19:16,192
Will, I don't have plans to commit suicide.

1345
01:19:16,280 --> 01:19:17,235
You don't?

1346
01:19:17,320 --> 01:19:18,912
Not at the moment, no.

1347
01:19:19,640 --> 01:19:21,949
Great. Great!

1348
01:19:22,040 --> 01:19:24,076
Good.

1349
01:19:24,160 --> 01:19:26,913
You know I'm not attracted to you, right?

1350
01:19:28,560 --> 01:19:31,791
What are you on about?
No. What are you, nuts?

1351
01:19:32,520 --> 01:19:34,636
Right. Wrong word completely.

1352
01:19:34,880 --> 01:19:39,670
But that's something that
we should, you know, talk about a bit.

1353
01:19:39,760 --> 01:19:41,990
The crying in the morning thing, the depression.

1354
01:19:42,080 --> 01:19:44,310
Let's get that fixed.

1355
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:47,358
FlONA: That's what men think, isn't it?
WlLL: What?

1356
01:19:47,880 --> 01:19:50,838
That unless you've got the answer,
unless you can say:

1357
01:19:50,920 --> 01:19:54,913
"l know a bloke in the Essex Road who
can fix that," then there's no point bothering.

1358
01:19:55,000 --> 01:19:55,955
No.

1359
01:19:57,320 --> 01:19:59,072
Well, yeah, okay. I would.

1360
01:19:59,160 --> 01:20:02,072
I'd love to know the name of the bloke
in the Essex Road...

1361
01:20:02,160 --> 01:20:04,390
...because I've got a feeling I'd be useless.

1362
01:20:04,480 --> 01:20:06,391
Will, you're not useless.

1363
01:20:07,640 --> 01:20:10,916
You're here. And that matters.

1364
01:20:11,840 --> 01:20:12,989
Right.

1365
01:20:13,080 --> 01:20:15,355
-Now, can we.... Do you mind?
-What?

1366
01:20:15,640 --> 01:20:19,030
-Marcus is singing at the school concert.
-Marcus is singing?

1367
01:20:19,120 --> 01:20:20,473
-Yeah, singing.
-At school?

1368
01:20:20,560 --> 01:20:22,118
It's a pop concert. He's so excited.

1369
01:20:22,200 --> 01:20:25,272
-I want to get there on time.
-Wait, wait. What's he singing?

1370
01:20:25,360 --> 01:20:29,592
[Sings] "Killing me softly with his song

1371
01:20:29,880 --> 01:20:32,314
"Telling my whole life"

1372
01:20:32,760 --> 01:20:34,352
[Tires screech]

1373
01:20:34,440 --> 01:20:38,069
-What time does this thing start?
-What have you got against Marcus singing?

1374
01:20:38,160 --> 01:20:42,472
You know the dream where you're at school
without your trousers on and everyone laughs?

1375
01:20:42,560 --> 01:20:45,597
-What's the connection?
-That will be Marcus, but for real.

1376
01:20:45,680 --> 01:20:48,274
If he sings that song in front of those kids...

1377
01:20:48,360 --> 01:20:50,555
...you can just write him off until university.

1378
01:20:50,640 --> 01:20:53,712
If he reaches university,
'cause he's going to get torn to shreds.

1379
01:20:53,800 --> 01:20:56,314
You cannot stop someone
from expressing themselves.

1380
01:20:56,400 --> 01:21:00,075
He's not expressing himself!
He's expressing you, okay?

1381
01:21:01,520 --> 01:21:02,589
Oh, God.

1382
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:07,070
What? Jesus Christ.

1383
01:21:07,360 --> 01:21:10,875
You're right. Will, am I a bad mother?

1384
01:21:11,280 --> 01:21:15,592
No, you're not a bad mother.
You're just a barking lunatic.

1385
01:21:15,760 --> 01:21:17,398
No, I am. I am a bad mother.

1386
01:21:17,480 --> 01:21:20,711
I've let things slide
and I haven't been noticing properly.

1387
01:21:20,800 --> 01:21:23,189
He's a special, very special boy.

1388
01:21:23,280 --> 01:21:25,669
And he's got a special soul, and I've wounded it!

1389
01:21:25,760 --> 01:21:28,513
Please, just shut up. You're wounding my soul.

1390
01:21:29,600 --> 01:21:32,194
[Light, easy instrumental music,
while car screeches]

1391
01:21:40,880 --> 01:21:43,678
[Music becomes faster and heavier]

1392
01:21:55,560 --> 01:21:57,790
WlLL: Okay, you park it.
FlONA: What?

1393
01:22:01,200 --> 01:22:03,794
[Rock song faster and more urgent]

1394
01:22:16,000 --> 01:22:19,197
[Tires squeal]

1395
01:22:20,160 --> 01:22:22,071
[Group sings hip hop song to music]

1396
01:22:43,800 --> 01:22:44,835
Hi.

1397
01:22:46,080 --> 01:22:47,399
What are you doing here?

1398
01:22:47,480 --> 01:22:49,232
That's Ali up there.

1399
01:22:54,880 --> 01:22:58,509
He's talented.

1400
01:23:11,400 --> 01:23:12,992
[Cheering]

1401
01:23:22,240 --> 01:23:27,189
Now that was the Def Penalty Kru
with Murder Fo' Life.

1402
01:23:27,880 --> 01:23:30,792
Our next big act is Marcus Brewer...

1403
01:23:30,880 --> 01:23:34,111
...singing Roberta Flack's beloved
Killing Me Softly.

1404
01:23:34,200 --> 01:23:35,792
[Laughter]

1405
01:23:36,600 --> 01:23:40,070
He'll be accompanied by Simon Cosgrove
on the recorder.

1406
01:23:42,320 --> 01:23:43,878
Marcus, I can't do this.

1407
01:23:43,960 --> 01:23:46,599
-That lot's going to shit all over us.
-But you said....

1408
01:23:46,680 --> 01:23:50,195
I'm sorry. Here's your $5 back.

1409
01:23:52,440 --> 01:23:53,919
Any moment now.

1410
01:23:54,000 --> 01:23:55,991
[Disgruntled chatter]

1411
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:10,154
Come on, Marcus, you wally!

1412
01:24:14,200 --> 01:24:15,235
Wait! Wait!

1413
01:24:15,320 --> 01:24:17,629
Excuse me. What is going on here?

1414
01:24:17,800 --> 01:24:21,236
Nothing. Everything's under control.
I'm just his voice coach.

1415
01:24:21,480 --> 01:24:22,913
What are you doing here?

1416
01:24:23,000 --> 01:24:27,278
I heard you were about to commit social suicide,
so I dropped by.

1417
01:24:27,360 --> 01:24:28,998
-My accompanist left!
-Brilliant.

1418
01:24:29,080 --> 01:24:30,877
-You don't have to do it.
-I can't do that.

1419
01:24:30,960 --> 01:24:33,713
Yeah, you can.
Just tell them: Artistic differences.

1420
01:24:33,800 --> 01:24:36,268
You can't work without him.
He had a drug problem.

1421
01:24:36,360 --> 01:24:38,555
My mum wants me to sing it.
It'll make her happy.

1422
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:43,589
Look, mate, nothing you do
can make your mum happy, all right?

1423
01:24:44,080 --> 01:24:47,595
Not in the long term.
She has to do that for herself.

1424
01:24:47,680 --> 01:24:51,195
-Get over here right now!
-Just bugger off, will you!

1425
01:24:51,320 --> 01:24:54,676
What I'm saying is, the important thing is
to make yourself feel happy.

1426
01:24:54,760 --> 01:24:58,514
I've tried just making myself happy.
She's tried making herself happy.

1427
01:24:58,680 --> 01:25:01,194
It doesn't work.
You need other people to make you happy.

1428
01:25:01,280 --> 01:25:02,599
But that's just it.

1429
01:25:02,680 --> 01:25:06,673
If other people can make you happy
then they can also make you unhappy.

1430
01:25:06,760 --> 01:25:10,230
What, you think those people out there
are going to make you happy?

1431
01:25:10,320 --> 01:25:12,038
Hang on. Wait. Marcus, don't.

1432
01:25:12,120 --> 01:25:14,350
Marcus! Bollocks.

1433
01:25:15,640 --> 01:25:17,631
[Clapping fades out]

1434
01:25:27,520 --> 01:25:29,909
[Poignant piano notes]

1435
01:25:31,200 --> 01:25:32,838
BULLY: Come on, Britney!

1436
01:25:33,000 --> 01:25:35,070
Yeah, give us a song, then.

1437
01:25:35,160 --> 01:25:36,639
[Laughter]

1438
01:25:41,960 --> 01:25:43,632
This is for my mum.

1439
01:25:49,280 --> 01:25:53,432
[Sings] "l heard he sang a good song

1440
01:25:54,440 --> 01:25:57,876
"l heard he had a style

1441
01:25:59,280 --> 01:26:02,989
"And so I came to see him

1442
01:26:03,160 --> 01:26:06,709
"to listen for a while

1443
01:26:08,360 --> 01:26:12,148
"And there he was this young boy

1444
01:26:12,960 --> 01:26:16,509
"a stranger to my eyes"

1445
01:26:16,600 --> 01:26:18,397
You're rubbish, mate!

1446
01:26:18,480 --> 01:26:20,072
[Laughter]

1447
